    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1913-10-19T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1913-10-19T00:00:00-05:00" n="1151"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1151">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.00/9275.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">American Chargé d’Affaires</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1913-10-19">
                            <hi rend="italic">October 19, 1913</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Consular Agent at Torreón instructed to make clear to the rebel authorities that
                    all foreigners desiring to leave should be permitted to do so unmolested. The
                    Agent was also instructed that the same protection we extend to American
                    citizens should be extended of nationals of foreign nations.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Bryan</hi>.</signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
